#: ../../M/meta-bit.rst:5
msgid "meta bit"
msgstr "meta bit"

#: ../../M/meta-bit.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../M/meta-bit.rst:9
msgid ""
"The top bit of an 8-bit character, which is on in character values 128--255."
" Also called :ref:`high-bit`\\, :ref:`alt-bit`\\. Some terminals and "
"consoles (see :ref:`space-cadet-keyboard`\\) have a META shift key. Others "
"(including, *mirabile dictu*\\, keyboards on IBM PC-class machines) have an "
"ALT key. See also :ref:`bucky-bits`\\."
msgstr ""
"8ビット文字の最上位ビット。文字値128〜255でオンになる。\\ :ref:`high-bit`\\ 、\\ :ref:`alt-bit`\\ "
"とも呼ばれる。一部の端末やコンソール(\\ :ref:`space-cadet-keyboard`\\ "
"を参照)はMETAシフトキーを持つ。他のもの(\\ *mirabile dictu*\\ 、IBM "
"PCクラスの機械のキーボードを含む)はALTキーを持つ。\\ :ref:`bucky-bits`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../M/meta-bit.rst:15
msgid ""
"Historical note: although in modern usage shaped by a universe of 8-bit "
"bytes the meta bit is invariably hex 80 (octal 0200), things were different "
"on earlier machines with 36-bit words and 9-bit bytes. The MIT and Stanford "
"keyboards (see :ref:`space-cadet-keyboard`\\) generated hex 100 (octal 400) "
"from their meta keys."
msgstr ""
"歴史的注記:8ビットバイトの宇宙によって形作られた現代の用法ではmeta "
"bitは必ず16進80(8進0200)だが、36ビットワードと9ビットバイトを持つ初期の機械では事情が違った。MITとStanfordのキーボード(\\"
" :ref:`space-cadet-keyboard`\\ を参照)はそのmetaキーから16進100(8進400)を生成した。"
